historischen und bibliographischen Material, darunter einzigartigem Archivmaterial, das hier zum ersten Mal aufbereitet wird.  aIn Libraries in Russia, the author, Valerii Leonov, pursues the history of the first Russian national library, the Library of the Russian Academy of Science (Bibliotheca Akademii Nauk, short: BAN), from the beginning of the 18th century to the present. The library was founded by Peter the Great in 1714 and served as a model for the foundation of further libraries during the 18th century. This historical description is based on extensive historical and bibliographic material, including unique archive material, which is edited here for the first time. The title will be of interest to all in the humanities and everyone interested in Russian history and culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aLibrarieszRussiaxHistory. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / General.2bisacsh1 aOstwald-Richter, Katrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aProkofiev, Mikhail A.1 aSherwood-Jenkins, Marcus A.1 aYashugin, Nikolai I.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Law 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062097908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Library Information Science 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062096208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Library Information Science 2000 - 2014z9783110636246oZDB-23-GLI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2005z9783110277111oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2005z978311027717308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyter